HEADWORD: Harts-tongue
<hw>Hart's"-tongue`</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rts"t⟦ucr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A common British fern
(<spn>Scolopendrium vulgare</spn>), rare in America.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A West Indian fern, the <spn>Polypodium Phyllitidis</spn> of
Linnaeus. It is also found in Florida.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

